1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:33,870 --> 00:01:34,820
Garp?!

3
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:37,080
He disappeared at the Pirate Island?!

4
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:38,490
Is that true?!

5
00:01:38,490 --> 00:01:42,000
He went there to go rescue
this Koby guy, didn't he?

6
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,880
He must've sacrificed himself for his friend...

7
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,750
It doesn't say he's dead!

8
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:50,130
He's a man with many legends to his name!

9
00:01:50,130 --> 00:01:51,840
Don't worry yourselves.

10
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,890
Very true, Mayor.

11
00:01:53,890 --> 00:01:55,390
Obviously.

12
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:00,100
Who's laughing?! What's so funny?!

13
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,560
Oh, goodness.

14
00:02:05,190 --> 00:02:07,070
That scared you, huh?

15
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:08,190
There, there...

16
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,940
Oh, it's just you...

17
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:11,150
I'm sorry, Makino.

18
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:14,780
I know you're worried about Garp.

19
00:02:14,780 --> 00:02:18,200
Recently, this little one has started
to recognize Luffy's face.

20
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:21,580
You love your big bro Luffy, don't you?

21
00:02:24,790 --> 00:02:26,630
Freakin' Garp and Luffy...

22
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:28,210
What are you doing?!

23
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:46,480
It's a big one!

24
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:52,940
It's an earthquake!

25
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,370
Daddy!

26
00:03:01,790 --> 00:03:04,160
There's a tsunami on the way!

27
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,750
Get to high ground!

28
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,710
Over here! Please hurry!

29
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:14,970
This one's huge!

30
00:03:17,510 --> 00:03:21,140
The earthquake on that day
was unprecedented in recorded history.

31
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:25,600
It left severe damage
in its wake across the world.

32
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:38,280
Run! Get to higher ground!

33
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:39,910
We're too late...

34
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:50,670
Its epicenter could not be detected,
making it a seismological anomaly.

35
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,090
Though the connection is unclear...

36
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:57,470
it happened six days after the Kingdom
of Lulusia was wiped off the map...

37
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,970
without anyone knowing about it.

38
00:03:59,970 --> 00:04:02,470
I'm here at the the former site of Lulusia!

39
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:04,930
There's no trace of land anymore!

40
00:04:04,930 --> 00:04:07,520
Only a giant hole with water pouring into it!

41
00:04:07,850 --> 00:04:09,690
No further approach is possible!

42
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:11,480
The hole shows no signs of filling!

43
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:19,700
The earthquake caused sea levels around
the world to rise by approximately one meter.

44
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,950
Vayyt! Vhaat is happening?!

45
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:32,590
The beach has never flooded like this!

46
00:04:32,590 --> 00:04:34,460
The tide vill ebb eventually, right?!

47
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:35,920
I can't take it!

48
00:04:36,670 --> 00:04:40,180
I wanted to run on the beach!

49
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:42,800
Come on!

50
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:45,680
Give us back our beach!

51
00:04:46,930 --> 00:04:50,140
A number of beaches around
the world have disappeared,

52
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:52,650
along with several islands.

53
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:57,320
We lost our home to the flood!

54
00:04:57,320 --> 00:05:00,280
A shark swam right into my house!

55
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:04,450
It's not supposed to be high tide yet!

56
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:06,450
Maybe today's catch will be huge.

57
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,700
No, idiot! Don't sail out in this!

58
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:14,000
Update regarding the global flooding...

59
00:05:15,130 --> 00:05:17,510
Sea levels are rising around the world?!

60
00:05:18,050 --> 00:05:19,050
Yes, sir.

61
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:20,930
I don't understand what's happening...

62
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:25,510
Meanwhile, in the New World...
Future Island, Egghead...

63
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:29,980
was surrounded by a fleet
of one hundred ships

64
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:32,440
—including twenty massive battleships—

65
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:36,480
that far outclassed the nation-sized fleet
a buster call could summon.

66
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:39,990
Aboard those ships were 30,000 Marines.

67
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,820
Leading this unprecedented military force...

68
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:52,620
were nine vice admirals
from Marine Headquarters...

69
00:05:59,170 --> 00:05:59,880
and...

70
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:03,090
Admiral Kizaru.

71
00:06:05,050 --> 00:06:07,050
Here they come!

72
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:43,720
Hey!

73
00:06:44,590 --> 00:06:48,180
Didn't I tell you not to attack
the weaponized sea beasts?!

74
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:52,390
Well, it attacked us first.

75
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:55,350
Kizaru, sir, your meal.

76
00:06:56,730 --> 00:06:59,150
Oh, looks good!

77
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,610
All yours!

78
00:07:00,610 --> 00:07:02,280
Chopsticks are over there!

79
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:13,830
Gotta say, I'm not sure I'm
comfortable with this, Sentomaru.

80
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:18,500
Why not surrender and come back to us?

81
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,840
You try that again, and we return fire, Unc!

82
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:24,340
That's real scary.

83
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:30,720
Old Man Punk developed the pacifista's
lasers by studying your abilities, y'know.

84
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,890
Whoa, awesome!

85
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:37,980
I never thought you'd come to
get rid of Old Man Punk...

86
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:44,860
Studying the Void Century is a crime
even I can't defend, Sentomaru.

87
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,200
I'm just...

88
00:07:46,650 --> 00:07:48,570
a cog in the machine.

89
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:54,540
It's not like we stand to gain anything
from this battle, either.

90
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:57,540
The more we destroy, the more we lose.

91
00:07:57,540 --> 00:08:01,880
Seems Rob Lucci's agents
couldn't get the job done.

92
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,300
Yeah, thanks to the Straw Hats.

93
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:12,260
Do not let them know that I am here.

94
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:13,220
Yes, sir.

95
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:18,690
"The Straw Hat Pirates took Vegapunk hostage
and barricaded themselves on the island," huh?

96
00:08:18,690 --> 00:08:20,350
Not a bad piece.

97
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:22,310
That would be Morgans'.

98
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:24,150
And what of the truth?

99
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:28,110
Sir! We have received no word that
CP0 has completed their mission.

100
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:32,070
Given that Sentomaru
is still defending the island...

101
00:08:32,530 --> 00:08:35,040
we know that the people in the Labophase are:

102
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:38,960
the main Dr. Vegapunk and his six satellites,

103
00:08:39,670 --> 00:08:42,750
the four seraphim protecting him,

104
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:48,010
and the ten members of Emperor
Straw Hat's crew, believed to be allied with them.

105
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:57,390
The commanders of CP0's lead unit,
Rob Lucci, Kaku, and Stussy...

106
00:08:57,390 --> 00:09:02,350
seem to have been captured alongside
other Cipher Pol agents by Sentomaru...

107
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:05,270
and his pacifista Mk. III units
in the Fabriophase.

108
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:11,410
The Frontier Dome's
barrier status is at 100 percent,

109
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:14,870
so entering or exiting
the Labophase is impossible.

110
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:20,920
It's been a full day, yet we still
have no intel on what's happening inside.

111
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:26,460
Where have the research staff
and technicians who work on Egghead gone?

112
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,880
As of yesterday, they've all evacuated.

113
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:32,180
We've already located their ships.

114
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,850
What if they know too much?

115
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,310
Sink them immediately.

116
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,060
Yes, sir!

117
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:41,230
St. Saturn, one more thing!

118
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:45,360
Jewelry Bonney the Glutton
has also been sighted on the island!

119
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,070
Kuma's daughter, eh?

120
00:09:47,610 --> 00:09:49,440
We have no further use for her.

121
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:54,240
Forget her. She is a mere girl.

122
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:54,910
Understood.

123
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:58,580
Kizaru, sir!

124
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:04,750
I'm in the middle of eating...

125
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:07,000
We're picking up a signal from Egghead!

126
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:10,380
Seems they're calling somewhere!

127
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:12,840
Just find out who they're calling, quickly.

128
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,220
It's Mary Geoise!

129
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,270
Who is this?

130
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:29,650
Admiral, that thing on your wrist
is a black wiretapper snail.

131
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:32,650
You can tap the call.

132
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,040
Hello?! It's me!

133
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,540
York!

134
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:46,670
Oh, it's you.

135
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:48,380
What are you doing?!

136
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:49,630
What's your problem?!

137
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:52,720
Why are you trying to kill me, too?!

138
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,890
I gave you the intel about Stella's betrayal!

139
00:10:56,390 --> 00:11:00,640
You are also a Vegapunk, York.

140
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:07,100
If I was interested in the Void Century,
there's no way I would've tattled on him!

141
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,060
How disappointing!

142
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:08,980
How disappointing!

143
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,900
That is true.

144
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,780
I am surprised you are alive.

145
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:15,990
Did CP0 not come?

146
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:19,410
What is the status of the Straw Hats?

147
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:23,450
The fact that I'm the only one
talking to you after last night...

148
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:25,410
The fact that I'm the only one
talking to you after last night...

149
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:28,790
should tell you everything!

150
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:33,760
Egghead is all mine now!

151
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:37,260
I've got the seraphim!

152
00:11:38,090 --> 00:11:38,800
So...

153
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:41,810
what's with the fleet surrounding the island?

154
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:44,600
You wanna go to war with me?

155
00:11:45,060 --> 00:11:48,230
York, we have had a change of heart.

156
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:54,490
You are able to create this so-called
Mother Flame as well, are you not?

157
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:02,080
Oh, so now you wanna play along?

158
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,750
I knew you'd want it!

159
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:06,540
Glad I sent it to you.

160
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:09,500
Yes, it is desired.

161
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,090
Desired?

162
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:12,460
By who?

163
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:15,460
The power plant used to
make it is here on the island.

164
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,640
Listen up.

165
00:12:28,020 --> 00:12:31,980
Promise me you won't hurt me or the lab.

166
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,400
We promise.

167
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:36,150
And make me a Celestial Dragon!

168
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:37,860
Consider it done.

169
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,820
Then you've got a deal!

170
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:43,030
So how about you guys...

171
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:47,250
hurry up and save me already?!

172
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:52,500
Straw Hat Luffy is gonna kill me!

173
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:53,880
– What?!
– What?!

174
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:54,750
What is this?!

175
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:56,460
What's happening?

176
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,260
Hey, Luffy!

177
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:03,470
What do we do with her?

178
00:13:03,470 --> 00:13:05,220
She's no use to us anymore.

179
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:12,190
Come crush these lunatics!

180
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:15,360
That's what was happening, huh?

181
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:17,440
Sorry for all the trouble we caused.

182
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:21,700
So that's how it is.
I'm starting to see the full picture.

183
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:23,410
Luffy, what should we do with her?

184
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:28,160
I dunno...

185
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,540
Use her as a shield to escape or something?

186
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:32,960
This is kinda like a hostage situation.

187
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,880
How are Robin's injuries?

188
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:39,840
They'll take some time to heal,
but she'll be fine as long as she rests.

189
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:45,010
Hello?!

190
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:47,220
My name is...

191
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:47,970
My name is...

192
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:50,350
Monkey D. Luffy!

193
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:52,600
The man who's gonna be King of the Pirates!

194
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,190
Wait, wait, Luffy! What are you saying?!

195
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:58,900
We've got Dr. Vegapunk!

196
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:01,860
If you value York's life,

197
00:14:01,860 --> 00:14:06,080
get all the Marine ships away from the shore!

198
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,830
Help me!

199
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:10,290
Straw Hat's gonna kill me!

200
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:13,170
He's pure evil!

201
00:14:13,170 --> 00:14:15,880
He's as vicious as they say...

202
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,460
The hell is he doing?!

203
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:20,840
What?! Luffy?!

204
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,420
What's going on over there?!

205
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:25,220
You would be Straw Hat Luffy?

206
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:29,770
Who is still alive on Egghead?

207
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:33,850
Well, let's see... We've got
some injured people, and...

208
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:36,020
Luffy, no!

209
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:41,070
A woman's voice...

210
00:14:41,490 --> 00:14:43,240
Nico Robin's, perhaps?

211
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,360
What was that for?!

212
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:47,240
Information is a weapon.

213
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:49,120
You must not hand it over so easily.

214
00:14:49,870 --> 00:14:51,200
Gotcha. Sorry.

215
00:14:51,580 --> 00:14:53,710
But now the ships are gonna be gone!

216
00:14:53,710 --> 00:14:54,920
Oh, like hell!

217
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:57,580
You think the Marines are that dumb?!

218
00:14:59,590 --> 00:15:01,090
St. Saturn...

219
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:03,300
There are three things we must protect.

220
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,550
York's safety.

221
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:08,010
Their brain, Punk Records.

222
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,640
The power plant that creates
the Mother Flame.

223
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,060
All else is expendable.

224
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:20,150
But Rob Lucci and the other
Cipher Pol agents are still inside of...

225
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:22,480
I speak only of a worst-case scenario.

226
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:25,820
Don't lose sight of our highest priorities.

227
00:15:27,110 --> 00:15:30,870
You'd do well to consider human lives
as nothing more than insects.

228
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:33,500
Even with dwindling numbers,
they recover quickly.

229
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:39,840
Yes, sir!

230
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,130
All of you, listen here!

231
00:15:43,130 --> 00:15:46,260
Touch me and the Five Elders
will obliterate the island!

232
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:49,510
They promised! Got that, morons?!

233
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:51,390
It'll be another Ohara!

234
00:16:01,690 --> 00:16:03,280
Owie!

235
00:16:03,780 --> 00:16:05,150
You asked for it!

236
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,150
I'm telling the Five Elders!

237
00:16:07,150 --> 00:16:09,360
Be my guest!

238
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:13,200
You've got some nerve saying something
like that in front of Robin!

239
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:16,080
You're the one asking for it here!

240
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:18,790
Chill out. She's unarmed.

241
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:22,380
Robin, are you feeling okay?

242
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:25,880
Yes, thanks to you, Chopper.

243
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:29,090
You're not making me happy, you dummy!

244
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,850
This is the pits!

245
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:37,180
But I was against two seraphim
at the same time.

246
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,770
Just sleep.

247
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,900
Shaka!

248
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,900
Pythagoras!

249
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,280
Edison!

250
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,910
Edison's still alive, Lilith!

251
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,490
Oh, thank goodness!

252
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,250
Keep it down, Lilith.

253
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,210
I'm trying to contact the basement.

254
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:04,710
Hey, you guys behaving down there?

255
00:17:04,710 --> 00:17:06,920
Straw Hats!

256
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:10,680
Thanks so much for the food!

257
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,600
You guys saved our lives!

258
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,350
So good!

259
00:17:15,350 --> 00:17:16,720
I feel alive again!

260
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:20,980
I'm feeling great thanks to you guys!

261
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:23,110
Hey, they're our enemies!

262
00:17:23,110 --> 00:17:24,310
Keep your voice down.

263
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:26,980
Now just let us out of here!

264
00:17:26,980 --> 00:17:30,950
I'm glad you guys are feeling better,
but that's a little too much to ask.

265
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:33,530
Then, could you at least relocate us?

266
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:37,450
Hard to relax with those things around...

267
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:40,080
There a problem down there?

268
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:43,080
I thought the seraphim were on your side.

269
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:46,300
Yeah, but in case they go berserk...

270
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:49,050
It'll be fine, right, Vegapunk?

271
00:17:49,050 --> 00:17:50,260
Certainly.

272
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:53,050
Those bubble balls

273
00:17:53,050 --> 00:17:57,310
are made of the same material
as the pacifista Mk. III's bubble shields,

274
00:17:57,310 --> 00:17:59,730
which are rated for cannon fire.

275
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:03,520
They're infused with sea energy,

276
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:07,770
making them perfect weapons
for trapping those with powers.

277
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:10,940
Ah, I see... I thought they were
just ordinary bubbles...

278
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,910
You dare to trap me in this thing?

279
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:17,410
There's no need to fear us.

280
00:18:17,410 --> 00:18:21,120
None of us were ordered to kill you.

281
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:23,540
We have no interest in you!

282
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,750
Y-You don't say...

283
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,840
Then there's no reason to worry...

284
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:33,090
But I really gotta thank you, S-Snake!

285
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:37,050
You undid our petrifications!

286
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,930
Did she, now?

287
00:18:38,930 --> 00:18:40,060
Peculiar...

288
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:43,890
I never programmed S-Snake to do that...

289
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,900
Hey, Hancock!

290
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,900
Those guys are my friends!

291
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,440
You gotta turn 'em back!

292
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,110
What?

293
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:54,450
You're the only one who can save them!

294
00:18:54,450 --> 00:18:55,410
Please!

295
00:18:57,820 --> 00:18:59,990
F-Fine!

296
00:18:59,990 --> 00:19:04,000
I will, so please stop looking at me...

297
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:06,750
Oh, is that what happened?

298
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:11,760
Well, even the original Hancock,
awful as she is, has a soft spot for Luffy.

299
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:14,010
How funny!

300
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,510
Her seraphim is the same way!

301
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:19,810
Oh, Hancock!

302
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:21,720
Hancock!

303
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:22,720
Hey!

304
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:25,390
I'm over here, Hancock!

305
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:26,850
Hey, over here!

306
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:25,390
The information transmitted through
the hereditary elements when producing clones...

307
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:26,850
is quite interesting!

308
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:30,360
I seriously owe you, Hancock!

309
00:19:30,360 --> 00:19:34,070
Owe you... Owe you... Owe you...

310
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:35,200
What?

311
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,570
Did you just say "I love you"?!

312
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,160
Stella!

313
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:49,040
The communications system
has been restored,

314
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,920
but the Frontier Dome still won't open!

315
00:19:53,170 --> 00:19:54,800
It's no use!

316
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:58,010
I protected it with a passcode.

317
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:00,600
But my brain's not synced
with the rest of yours,

318
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,350
and I'm not telling!

319
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:04,100
Oh yeah?!

320
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:06,390
Let's just see about that!

321
00:20:06,390 --> 00:20:08,730
Cool it, Lilith!

322
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:13,820
I'm being protected by both
the code and the world itself.

323
00:20:13,820 --> 00:20:16,280
Boy, I'm hungry...

324
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,490
Why, you little...!

325
00:20:18,860 --> 00:20:21,740
If we can't deactivate the barrier,
then there's no escape.

326
00:20:21,740 --> 00:20:25,500
Seriously? Even after
all my expert negotiating?

327
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,500
I told you that didn't help.

328
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:36,630
Four seriously injured...

329
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:38,760
Two of Vegapunk's satellites dead...

330
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,890
And the Straw Hats are...

331
00:20:41,890 --> 00:20:44,350
Penny for your thoughts, Lucci?

332
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,180
Just mumbling to myself.

333
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:54,320
We're surrounded on all sides, Stella.

334
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,320
Mistress Stussy!

335
00:20:56,320 --> 00:21:00,530
There are about 100 ships of various sizes
and 30,000 soldiers out there.

336
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,280
Quite the pickle.

337
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:05,830
Welcome back, Mistress Stussy!

338
00:21:05,830 --> 00:21:07,910
How about a coffee?

339
00:21:07,910 --> 00:21:09,000
Why, thank you.

340
00:21:10,830 --> 00:21:12,460
Don't give me that look.

341
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:15,750
So you would be Nami, the navigator?

342
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:17,460
Yep, that's me!

343
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:19,420
Tell me a bit about our route.

344
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:22,180
The log pose hasn't recorded the signal yet,

345
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:24,640
but we have one steady needle from Wano.

346
00:21:25,010 --> 00:21:26,930
It's pointing northeast...

347
00:21:26,930 --> 00:21:28,850
Ah, to Elbaph, then.

348
00:21:28,850 --> 00:21:31,060
– Elbaph?!
– Elbaph?!

349
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:32,230
Are we going there?!

350
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:33,560
Finally?!

351
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,940
Seems like it.

352
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:36,730
– Our long awaited...
– Our long awaited...

353
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:41,070
– Isle of Giants!
– Isle of Giants!

354
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:44,410
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph! ♪
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph! ♪

355
00:21:44,410 --> 00:21:49,040
♪ Everyone's huge, 'cause they're giants! ♪
♪ Everyone's huge, 'cause they're giants! ♪

356
00:21:44,410 --> 00:21:47,160
What's got them so excited?

357
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:51,750
Fortunately for us,

358
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:55,710
your ship is currently in the Labophase.

359
00:21:56,210 --> 00:21:59,210
The Marine ships are off
the shore in all directions.

360
00:21:59,210 --> 00:22:01,680
Sailing out of the port is impossible!

361
00:22:02,180 --> 00:22:04,390
We'd be heading northeast,

362
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,100
which is at the island's backside.

363
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:10,730
Luckily, your ship is next to the Vegaforce-01.

364
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:16,190
We could use the Vegaforce-01
to fly over the Marines' blockade,

365
00:22:16,190 --> 00:22:20,690
but that robot can only fly
within the airspace over Egghead.

366
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:24,160
It'll plummet as soon as
it leaves that area.

367
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,240
That's not far enough to escape!

368
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,370
Wrong!

369
00:22:27,370 --> 00:22:32,370
When we hit that point, we'll use
the Sunny's Coup de Burst to fly farther!

370
00:22:32,370 --> 00:22:36,080
If we can make it at least a kilometer away,
no one's gonna catch us, right?

371
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,460
What?!

372
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:39,800
Your ship can fly that far?!

373
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,050
She flies on cola, baby!

374
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:43,550
On cola?!

375
00:22:43,930 --> 00:22:45,140
Mm-hm!

376
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,980
Perfect! We'll run with that!

377
00:22:54,980 --> 00:22:55,690
Damn straight!

378
00:22:56,610 --> 00:22:57,730
Lilith!

379
00:22:57,730 --> 00:22:59,730
Use the Vegaforce-01 to...

380
00:22:59,730 --> 00:23:01,230
Way ahead of you!

381
00:23:01,230 --> 00:23:04,320
Move Straw Hat's ship
to the island's rear, right?

382
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,200
Okay!

383
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:09,660
But first, we have to
deactivate the Frontier Dome.

384
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:12,160
You're not getting the code out of me!

385
00:23:19,710 --> 00:23:20,960
Let's get cracking!

386
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,710
– Never underestimate Vegapunk!
– Never underestimate Vegapunk!

387
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:27,050
Looks like we've got a plan in motion.

388
00:23:27,050 --> 00:23:31,140
I'm not so sure it'll work out
how we want it to, though...

389
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:36,060
We won't know until we try.

390
00:23:36,060 --> 00:23:37,060
True.

391
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:41,570
If you're headed over to
the Sunny, I'll go with you.

392
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:43,070
Me, too!

393
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:45,200
Let's hurry up and leave for Elbaph!

394
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,530
I'll help out, too!

395
00:23:47,030 --> 00:23:48,990
Oh, thanks!

396
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,870
Alright!

397
00:23:59,250 --> 00:24:02,630
The operation is a-go!

398
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,720
Let's hurry and get the ship around back!

399
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,220
The barrier could come down at any minute!

400
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:17,310
Right... Let's hope there
won't be any more problems.

401
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:19,690
Don't you want it to come down?

402
00:24:19,690 --> 00:24:23,150
Sure I do, but if we're able to slip through it,

403
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:26,490
it also means we're open
to the enemy's attacks.

404
00:24:26,490 --> 00:24:28,110
Ah, makes sense!

405
00:24:28,110 --> 00:24:32,450
This is actually my first time
leaving the island!

406
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:34,330
C'mon, this ain't a field trip!

407
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,290
Either way...

408
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,000
We need more food!

409
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,090
Seconded!

410
00:24:42,500 --> 00:24:44,840
We'll eat all of this in one day!

411
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:46,300
Let's get some more pizza!

412
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:48,300
All we need is cheese.

413
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:50,930
If we have the ingredients,
Sanji will make us pizza.

414
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:54,310
He's pretty handy, huh?

415
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:56,140
A good cook and a good fighter!

416
00:24:56,140 --> 00:24:57,390
Huh?

417
00:24:57,390 --> 00:25:01,350
What's with the super good mood
all of a sudden? It's kinda creepy.

418
00:25:01,350 --> 00:25:04,520
You were so mean to Apple Gramps before.

419
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:12,240
Yeah, I decided I'm not
gonna kill Vegapunk anymore.

420
00:25:14,530 --> 00:25:17,620
Nice. Is that why you were crying all night?

421
00:25:17,620 --> 00:25:19,500
I was not!

422
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:22,670
Transmission from Agent Rob Lucci!

423
00:25:23,210 --> 00:25:26,000
We have info about the situation in Egghead.

424
00:25:29,260 --> 00:25:31,260
Share this with all ships!

425
00:25:31,260 --> 00:25:32,050
Yes, sir!

426
00:25:38,730 --> 00:25:41,350
Did you hear that, Borsalino?

427
00:25:42,350 --> 00:25:43,560
I did.

428
00:25:44,190 --> 00:25:48,490
He was sure talking a big game,
as if he was in control,

429
00:25:48,490 --> 00:25:52,570
but it seems they're the ones trapped inside.

430
00:25:52,570 --> 00:25:56,620
The Frontier Dome is a laser
defense system, correct?

431
00:25:56,620 --> 00:25:58,870
You are light itself.

432
00:25:58,870 --> 00:26:00,120
Can you get inside?

433
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:02,620
In all honesty, I can...

434
00:26:02,620 --> 00:26:06,840
But a dear friend of mine
is defending Vegapunk below it.

435
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,960
Simply leap over him.

436
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:14,680
It wouldn't be cool of me to humiliate
a man so determined to stand in my way.

437
00:26:15,180 --> 00:26:18,390
Please, let me at least
stay true to my principles.

438
00:26:18,850 --> 00:26:22,850
Besides, if we attack them,

439
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:29,150
Sentomaru will order the countless
weaponized sea beasts and the fifty pacifista...

440
00:26:29,150 --> 00:26:32,570
to sink our ships.

441
00:26:32,570 --> 00:26:36,160
The damage would be catastrophic.

442
00:26:37,780 --> 00:26:39,620
Time is of the essence, then...

443
00:26:40,750 --> 00:26:42,830
Where is the power plant?

444
00:26:47,090 --> 00:26:50,710
Rob Lucci is a capable man.

445
00:26:50,710 --> 00:26:56,260
He sent us all the necessary information.

446
00:27:06,100 --> 00:27:11,820
– Prepare for battle!
– Prepare for battle!

447
00:27:12,190 --> 00:27:15,780
All Six Powers users, make for land
as soon as the battle commences!

448
00:27:15,780 --> 00:27:19,490
Free the captured Cipher Pol agents!

449
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:23,370
Artillery fire won't work on the pacifista!

450
00:27:23,370 --> 00:27:26,830
Aim for the weaponized sea beasts!

451
00:27:36,970 --> 00:27:39,220
This is super fun!

452
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:40,930
It's ground from a sky island!

453
00:27:43,770 --> 00:27:46,770
I get it, man, but we gotta get serious!

454
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,150
Look!

455
00:27:49,150 --> 00:27:50,820
There's the Sunny!

456
00:28:00,490 --> 00:28:02,200
Well then...

457
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,580
Sacred Yata Mirror.

458
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:26,020
You're finally here, Unc!

459
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:28,020
Pacifista!

460
00:28:43,740 --> 00:28:47,210
Here I come, Sentomaru!

461
00:28:49,750 --> 00:28:51,710
Bring it, Unc!

462
00:28:52,630 --> 00:28:55,340
My defense...

463
00:28:56,300 --> 00:28:59,430
is the greatest in the world!

464
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,940
Huh...?

465
00:29:10,940 --> 00:29:12,150
What's that?!

466
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:14,360
Light from below?!

467
00:29:17,610 --> 00:29:19,320
There's someone here!

468
00:29:20,150 --> 00:29:21,610
Someone strong!

